The farmer was sitting on the veranda of his house at Tatoon Farm in Bulwer, Midlands, when a group of unknown men attacked him. JOHANNESBURG - Police in KwaZulu-Natal say they are following tip-offs that could lead to the arrest of suspects who doused a 64-year-old farmer with petrol and set him alight. The farmer was sitting on the veranda of his house at Tatoon Farm in Bulwer, Midlands, when a group of unknown men attacked him.The victim was burnt beyond recognition. He was found by his wife and a friend who were not home during the incident.The police's Thulani Zwane says: We are still looking for suspects and appeal that anyone with information contact the police. Zwane says that a case of murder has been opened.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)